HEADWORD: forepole
<hw>fore"pole`</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧r"p⟦omac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>One of the thick laths or poles driven
horizontally ahead on top of a set of the main timbering in advancing a
level in loose ground.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> spile{4}; spill{2d}.</syn>⟦br⟧
